_comment: Spawn quality log. Each event records one spawn decision and its outcome.

_fields.frontier: which frontier question this advances (or null)
_fields.two_phase: true if discovery agent preceded partition agents (P-119)
_fields.findings_per_agent: count of distinct findings per agent [n1, n2, ...]
_fields.cross_agent_unique: findings only possible from multi-agent comparison

spawn_events.task_description: F71 test: 2-agent partition on architecture question (method vs data decomposition)
missed_dimensions: architecture dimension found only by single agent post-hoc
spawn_events.notes: Partition without discovery failed. 2-agent split missed architecture dimension that single agent found. 2.3x tool call overhead for no marginal novelty. Source: P-119, L-114.

spawn_events.task_description: F107 genesis feedback: 3 reporter agents on genesis atom usage
spawn_events.notes: High convergence on genesis atoms (all 3 reporters agree). Convergent density confirms unanimous findings. Session-1-only limitation identified: belief-tracking and distill-protocol ignored in S1 but load-bearing at S3+. Source: f107-genesis-ablation.md.

spawn_events.task_description: F104 personality test: skeptic + explorer on F76/F100 analysis
spawn_events.notes: Complementary personalities produced qualitatively different outputs: skeptic defined minimum evidence bar (n=3 bugs insufficient, collinear with contract-type), explorer generated 5 new mechanisms to test (gofail density, error topology, temporal contract). Together = correct epistemic state. Explorer alone = unchallenged hypotheses. Skeptic alone = analysis paralysis. Source: P-116, L-111.

spawn_events.task_description: F103: 3-agent colony on repo analysis (dutch + complexity_ising_idea)
spawn_events.notes: NK found structure findings, EH found error handling patterns, Verification found cross-agent convergence signal. 2 findings were only possible because multiple agents compared notes. 3rd agent (verification) added 1 unique cross-agent finding. Wall-time 2.2x faster than sequential. Source: P-114, L-110.
